---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Layout>
  <div class="max-w-7xl  mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 lg:py-20">
    <div class="text-center mb-16 lg:mb-24">
      <h1
        class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl lg:text-7xl xl:text-8xl font-black mb-6"
        style="text-shadow: 3px 3px 0 #29cb17, -2px -2px 0 #0a4b09, 3px -2px 0 #406f40, -2px 3px 0 #75db77;"
      >
        My projects
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl text-[#29cb17] max-w-4xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Stay updated on my latest projects — from art to branding.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- PROJECT 1 -->
    <div class="mb-16 lg:mb-24">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-black via-[#1a1010] to-black rounded-2xl overflow-hidden shadow-[0_20px_60px_rgba(0,0,0,0.9)] border border-gray-800 hover:border-lime-500/30 transition-all duration-500">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-0">
          <!-- Image -->
          <div class="order-1 relative overflow-hidden h-[400px] lg:h-auto group">
            <img
              src="/Billeder/PH.png"
              alt="Haunted House Tour"
              class="w-full h-full object-cover transition-transform duration-700 group-hover:scale-110"
            />
            <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-black/60 to-transparent lg:opacity-80"></div>
          </div>

          <!-- Content -->
          <div class="order-2 p-8 lg:p-12 xl:p-16 flex flex-col justify-center">
            <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-[#29cb17] mb-6">
              Project nr. 1
            </h2>

<div class="space-y-4 text-lg text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-8">
  <p>
    <strong class="text-[#29cb17]">Fragments of Silence</strong> is a conceptual art project exploring the tension between chaos and stillness in modern digital life. Through layered textures, distorted forms, and muted color palettes, the piece reflects how silence can exist even in overwhelming noise.
  </p>

  <p>
    The work combinesdigital collage, 3D elements, and motion-based experimentatio to create a fragmented visual narrative. Each composition is intentionally imperfect — broken lines, abrupt transitions, and visual glitches are used as a language rather than flaws.
  </p>

  <p>
    The project was developed as an exploration of identity in a hyper-connected world, where constant input often leads to emotional detachment. By stripping away clarity and introducing visual tension, the viewer is invited to pause and interpret the work in their own way.
  </p>
</div>
